      "full_name": "Toronto Maple Leafs",
      "league": "NHL",
      "record": "32-36-14",
      "detail": "8th in Atlantic Division",
      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Leafs",
        "body": "The curtain crashed down on another Toronto season of familiar frustration - 32-36-14, eighth in the Atlantic, a yawning 31 points back and reeling from <strong>L7</strong> to cap 78 points of mediocrity. No playoffs, no miracles, just the cold math of a 15th seed that leaves the faithful nursing hangovers from half-empty Scotiabank Arena. What went wrong? The core talent flickered but never ignited, defense leaked like a sieve, and goaltending crumbled under pressure - same old story, different year. <strong>Mats Sundin's return as executive adviser and John Chayka's shocking install as GM on May 3</strong> signals a front-office gut punch, trading nostalgia for analytics wizardry in a desperate bid to reboot. Chayka's youth - barely 37 - brings edge to a franchise starved for bold, while Sundin's gravitas whispers redemption for the ghosts of 2004. Watch Auston Matthews, still the supernova at 29, licking wounds from a campaign that demanded more; his summer shape will dictate the vibe. The real reckoning looms: free agency bloodbath, draft lottery ping-pong at No. 15, and whispers of coaching upheaval. <strong>Chayka's first trade deadline - er, summer window - will define if Leafs Nation dares dream again</strong>, or if it's rinse, repeat, reload.",
        "updated": "Updated May 4, 2026"
      },
